ce:section.ce:para:
The preparation of ultra-high fluorescent Ginkgo biloba-based CQDs undergoes a hydrothermal carbonisation process without any chemical additives, thus perfectly conforming to the purpose of green synthesis (Fig. 1
                        ). Ginkgo wood, bark and leaf powder (2.4 g) and deionized water (50 mL) were poured into a beaker and fully stirred. A stainless-steel autoclave with a Teflon liner (100 mL) in an oil bath pot was then used to sterilize the mixture for 8 h at 180 °C. The mixture was cooled to room temperature. Then, the mixture was centrifuged at 10,000 r/min for 15 min and the supernatant fluid was collected for further use. Finally, the supernatant fluid was filtered using a 0.22 μm disposable needle filter and poured into dialysis bags with molecular weight cutoff (MWCO): 1000 Da for 24 h. The purified CQDs solution was obtained [23]. To further achieve ultra-high PL intensity of CQDs, we employed diverse preparation parameters to prepare CQDs, including temperature, time and concentration (Table 1
                        ). The synthesis was the same as above. The CQDs powder was then collected from the solution after freeze-drying for subsequent testing.
